OL,6,FA fifth (20%) of financially pinched
OL,7,Fparents felt "embarrassed" about
OL,8,Fstruggling to pay for trips for their
OL,9,Fchildren.
OL,11,FDespite cost concerns, more than a
OL,12,Fthird (35%) of parents believed school
OL,13,Ftrips are critical to their child's
OL,14,Feducation.
OL,16,FTilden Watson, head of education at
OL,17,FZurich Municipal, said: "School trips
OL,18,Fbring a plethora of benefits to young
OL,19,Flives, it's heartbreaking to see so
OL,20,Fmany could miss out due to cost.
