OL,6,F"These trips can also expose some
OL,7,Fchildren to new places and experiences
OL,8,Fthat they wouldn't necessarily get to
OL,9,Fenjoy with their families so they
OL,10,Freally do offer a window to the world
OL,11,Fthey otherwise wouldn't see."
OL,13,FOnePoll surveyed 1,000 parents of
OL,14,Fchildren aged five to 16 across the UK
OL,15,Fin May.
OL,17,FSome parents may be able to get help
OL,18,Fwith school-related costs, such as for
OL,19,Fmeals, transport and uniforms.
